\pagebreakNum

## Chaos Arts

#### Blur 
You may invoke Chaos as a bonus action to warp the air around you; you are considered to be behind half cover until the start of your next turn.

#### Chaos Brand
When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, you can invoke Chaos and brand them until the start of your next turn. While branded, any damage they receive from spells is increased by one roll of your Chaos Die. 

#### Chaos Nova 
Once per turn, when you hit a creature with a weapon attack, you can invoke Chaos to force the creature to succeed on a Constitution saving throw against your Chaos save DC or gain one level of exhaustion. This exhaustion last until the creature regains hit points or until it succeeds on the Constitution saving throw, which it can reroll at the end of each of its turns. 

#### CLeansed in Flames
When you start your turn while affected by the frightened or charmed condition, you can invoke Chaos to reroll the saving throw. If your result is 4 or more, you make this saving throw with advantage. 

#### Consume Magic
When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, you can attempt to consume the residual magic on a creature. You can invoke Chaos, and if the result is equal to or greater than twice the level of the an active spell on the creature, the spell ends on them, and you gain temporary hit points equal to the 5 times the spell's level

#### Deflect
When you are targeted for an attack, you can invoke Chaos and add half the result to your AC for that attack, possibly turning a hit into a miss.  

#### Disrupt
When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, you can invoke Chaos and disrupt their ability to cast spells. Until the start of your next turn, whenever the creature attempts to cast a spell, they take one Chaos Die of damage

#### Fel Enhancement
When you make an ability check, you can invoke Chaos and add it to the result. 

#### Imprison
When you hit a humanoid, beast, or fiend with a weapon attack, you can invoke Chaos, and if the creature's CR is equal to or less than the roll, the creature is incapacitated until the start of your next turn. 

#### Torment 
As an action, you can invoke Chaos to inflict a creature you can see within 60 feet of you with perpetual torment which must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes one Chaos die of damage, and has disadvantage on all attack rolls against targets other than you until the end of your next turn. In addition, whenever the creature attacks another creature but you, they take damage equal to your Charisma modifier.


\pagebreak

#### Old Content

#### Vengeful Retreat
Starting at 13th level, you learn to take creature advantage of moving away from your foes. Once per turn, when you would gain the benefit of the Disengage action, you may dismiss your Chaos Form to make one weapon attack as a part of that action.

#### Immolation Aura
Starting at 17th level, you can invoke an aura of fierce chaos energies inside you in your demonic form. When you use your Metamorphosis feature, and as a bonus action for its duration, you can force each creature within 10 feet to make a Dexterity saving throw (DC = 8 + prof + your Charisma modifier), taking 1d10 chaos damage on a fail, or half as much on a success.

#### Demonic Knowledge
Starting at 3rd level, you gain greater knowledge of fel and demonic forces. You gain proficiency in the Arcana skill, and whenever you would make an Intelligence or Wisdom ability check that pertains to fiends or demons, you may use your Charisma modifier for this ability check. 


#### Sigil of Suppression
At 13th level, you are able to suppress the magical abilities of a creature hit by your chaos flames. When you hit a creature with your Chaos Flames, you can choose to mark them with this sigil. This sigil last for 1 hour, or until you dismiss it (no action required). You can use your reaction when the creature casts a spell, creating the effects of a *counterspell* spell on the creature. You use Charisma as your spellcasting modifier for the sake of this feature, and if you need to make an ability check for this spell, you may add one Chaos Die to the check. 

You can use this feature twice, and regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest. 

